The paper deals with authentication in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security (cs.CR). The use of multiple sensor nodes and a fusion center suggests a system-level approach, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY). The use of compressed sensing to reduce reporting overhead involves signal processing (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI).
